Everything's implemented and verified. Here's a summary of the changes:

**`app/auth.py`** — `require_api_key` now checks for a missing/invalid `X-API-Key` header and raises HTTP 401 with `"Invalid or missing API key"`, returning the username on success.

**`app/main.py`** — all 6 features done:

| Endpoint | Changes |
|---|---|
| `GET /tasks` | Added optional `status`, `priority`, `assigned_to` query filters. Added `page` (default 1) and `page_size` (default 20, max 100) pagination. |
| `POST /tasks` | Requires `Depends(require_api_key)`. Validates `project_id` exists (404 if not). Auto-generates integer IDs. Returns 201 with the created task. |
| `PUT /tasks/{task_id}` | Requires auth. Uses `TaskUpdate.model_dump(exclude_unset=True)` for partial updates. Returns 404 if not found. |
| `DELETE /tasks/{task_id}` | Requires auth. Returns 204 on success, 404 if not found. |

